name: Contemplating Cumulus Clouds 1
description:
“Clouds come floating into my life, no longer to carry rain or usher storm, but to add color to my sunset sky.” ~ Rabindranath Tagore

This painting was created in water colors in Nov'2021 on ivory paper sheet. It is a series of three paintings. 

Please connect with me on twitter @singh99abhay or email me-  abhay99.tez@gmail.com if you wish to know more about this painting.
